results.name: Number of binary matrices with a total of n ones, distinct columns each with the same number of ones and distinct nonzero rows in decreasing lexicographic order.
comment: The condition that the rows be in decreasing order is equivalent to considering nonequivalent matrices with distinct rows up to permutation of rows.
